solution:
Without restriction, suppose $a \geqslant b \geqslant c$. By applying the rearrangement inequality twice:

$$
\begin{aligned}
& \frac{c}{a+b}+\frac{b}{a+c}+\frac{a}{c+b} \geqslant \frac{b}{a+b}+\frac{a}{a+c}+\frac{c}{c+b} \\
& \frac{c}{a+b}+\frac{b}{a+c}+\frac{a}{c+b} \geqslant \frac{a}{a+b}+\frac{c}{a+c}+\frac{b}{c+b}
\end{aligned}
$$

It then suffices to add the two inequalities to obtain the desired formula.
